    "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR introduces explicit global memory load/store intrinsics with various vector widths for fine-grained control over memory operations:\n\n- **Load intrinsics**: `ldg32`, `ldg64`, `ldg128`, `ldg256` - Load 32/64/128/256 bits from global memory\n- **Store intrinsics**: `stg32`, `stg64`, `stg128`, `stg256` - Store 32/64/128/256 bits to global memory\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **Predicated operations**: All intrinsics support optional predicates for conditional execution\n  ```python\n  val = T.ldg128(X[i:i+4], pred=i < N)  # Only load when predicate is true\n  T.stg128(Y[i:i+4], val, pred=i < N)   # Only store when predicate is true\n  ```\n\n- **CUDA version compatibility**: 256-bit operations include fallback for CUDA < 12.9\n  - CUDA 12.9+: Native `v4.u64` instructions\n  - CUDA < 12.9: Two `v4.u32` operations\n\n- **Return types**:\n  - `ldg32` → `uint32_t`\n  - `ldg64` → `uint2`\n  - `ldg128` → `uint4`\n  - `ldg256` → `ulonglong4`\n\n### Usage Example\n\n```python\n@tilelang.jit\ndef copy_kernel(X, Y):\n    N = T.const(\"N\")\n    X: T.Tensor[[N], T.float32]\n    Y: T.Tensor[[N], T.float32]\n\n    with T.Kernel(N // 4, threads=32) as pid:\n        # Load 128 bits (4 x float32)\n        val = T.ldg128(X[pid * 4: pid * 4 + 4])\n        # Store 128 bits\n        T.stg128(Y[pid * 4: pid * 4 + 4], val)\n```\n\n## Files Changed\n\n- `src/op/builtin.{cc,h}` - TIR op registration\n- `src/target/codegen_cuda.cc` - CUDA code generation\n- `src/tl_templates/cuda/copy.h` - PTX template implementations (ldg/stg 32/64/128)\n- `src/tl_templates/cuda/copy_sm100.h` - 256-bit operations with CUDA version fallback\n- `tilelang/language/builtin.py` - Python API\n- `tilelang/language/__init__.py` - Export functions\n- `testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_ldg.py` - Load tests\n- `testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_stg.py` - Store tests\n\n## Test Plan\n\n- [x] `test_ldg32_codegen` / `test_ldg32_predicated_codegen`\n- [x] `test_ldg64_codegen` / `test_ldg64_predicated_codegen`\n- [x] `test_ldg128_codegen` / `test_ldg128_predicated_codegen`\n- [x] `test_ldg256_codegen` / `test_ldg256_predicated_codegen`\n- [x] `test_stg32_codegen` / `test_stg32_predicated_codegen`\n- [x] `test_stg64_codegen` / `test_stg64_predicated_codegen`\n- [x] `test_stg128_codegen` / `test_stg128_predicated_codegen`\n- [x] `test_stg256_codegen` / `test_stg256_predicated_codegen`\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added explicit 32/64/128/256-bit global memory load/store intrinsics (with predicated variants), CUDA codegen support, a configurable lowering pass (predicated/non‑predicated modes), and a JIT helper to retrieve generated kernel source.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added unit and E2E tests validating intrinsics, predicated forms, codegen emission, lowering behavior, async/target guards, and CUDA integration.\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Expanded language exports, added a buffer-dtype helper, removed an obsolete utility, updated transform pipeline, and bumped a third‑party submodule.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
